issue.body:
~~Pointer inference is more tolerant and warns~~  
_report error_ about likely mishaps
with $ref to non schema objects in spec.

More edge case UT for schema analysis (explore error cases).

Extended golangci limit for cyclomatic check.

> NOTE: go-swagger/go-swagger#1602 is actually caused by an invalid spec.

body: With this fix and using --with-flatten=verbose, you should get a warning about what is likely to be a wrong $ref. However, the flatten shall recover from this by assuming you mean the underlying response schema.

Just improve the error message.
